.TH "spi_mem_get_name" 9 "spi_mem_get_name" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
spi_mem_get_name \- Return the SPI mem device name to be used by the upper layer if necessary
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "const char *" spi_mem_get_name
.BI "(struct spi_mem *mem "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mem" 12
the SPI memory
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function allows SPI mem users to retrieve the SPI mem device name.
It is useful if the upper layer needs to expose a custom name for
compatibility reasons.
.SH "RETURN"
a string containing the name of the memory device to be used
by the SPI mem user
